    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractUiWidgetIntegerField, UiWidgetIntegerFieldGwt, UiWidgetIntegerFieldTestImpl

    public interface UiWidgetIntegerField
extends UiWidgetTextualInputField<Integer>, UiWidgetRangeField<Integer>, UiWidgetNative
    This is the interface for a input field widget that represents an Integer field. Such field allows to enter a value of the type Integer. For advanced usability the widget shall be a so called spin box that has small arrows to increase and decrease the current value. However, this widget exists in order to expose native support for this feature (that might have advanced features or better performance). If this is not available by the underlying native toolkit, an implementation shall be provided that is based on UiWidgetTextField.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
